</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mweQ">It is then said that an amount of entropy <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt68" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"Δ&apos;&apos;S&apos;&apos;′"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mweg">Δ<i>S</i>′</span> has been transferred from the surroundings to the system. Because entropy is not a conserved quantity, this is an exception to the general way of speaking, in which an amount transferred is of a conserved quantity.</p>

<p id="mwew">From the second law of thermodynamics follows that in a spontaneous transfer of heat, in which the temperature of the system is different from that of the surroundings:</p>

<dl id="mwfA"><dd id="mwfQ"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt472" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":" \\Delta S_{\\mathrm{overall}}>0 ."}}' id="mwfg"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \Delta S_{\mathrm {overall} }>0.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ<!-- Δ --></mi>
        <msub>
          <mi>S</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">v</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>></mo>
        <mn>0.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \Delta S_{\mathrm {overall} }>0.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/46c43e4edf5a25eb0792cd9cbfc04935b97c1c2d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:13.302ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="\Delta S_{\mathrm {overall} }>0."/></span><span about="#mwt472">
</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwfw">For purposes of mathematical analysis of transfers, one thinks of fictive processes that are called <i id="mwgA">reversible</i>, with the temperature <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt70" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;T&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwgQ"><i>T</i></span> of the system being hardly less than that of the surroundings, and the transfer taking place at an imperceptibly slow rate.</p>

<p id="mwgg">Following the definition above in formula (1), for such a fictive reversible process, a quantity of transferred heat <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt71" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"δ&apos;&apos;Q&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwgw">δ<i>Q</i></span> (an <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Inexact_differential" title="Inexact differential" id="mwhA">inexact differential</a>) is analyzed as a quantity <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt72" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;T&apos;&apos; d&apos;&apos;S&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwhQ"><i>T</i> d<i>S</i></span>, with <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt73" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"d&apos;&apos;S&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwhg">d<i>S</i></span> (an <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Exact_differential" title="Exact differential" id="mwhw">exact differential</a>):</p>

<dl id="mwiA"><dd id="mwiQ"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt474" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":" T\\,\\mathrm{d}S=\\delta Q ."}}' id="mwig"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle T\,\mathrm {d} S=\delta Q.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>T</mi>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mi>S</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mi>δ<!-- δ --></mi>
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle T\,\mathrm {d} S=\delta Q.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/066fc5d3ecca4a70a6270a9596140b8c4f742939" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:11.447ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="T\,\mathrm {d} S=\delta Q."/></span><span about="#mwt474">
</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwiw">This equality is only valid for a fictive transfer in which there is no production of entropy, that is to say, in which there is no uncompensated entropy.</p>

<p id="mwjA">If, in contrast, the process is natural, and can really occur, with irreversibility, then there is <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Entropy_production" title="Entropy production" id="mwjQ">entropy production</a>, with <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt75" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"d&apos;&apos;S&apos;&apos;&lt;sub>uncompensated&lt;/sub> > 0"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwjg">d<i>S</i><sub>uncompensated</sub> > 0</span>. The quantity <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt76" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;T&apos;&apos; d&apos;&apos;S&apos;&apos;&lt;sub>uncompensated&lt;/sub>"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwjw"><i>T</i> d<i>S</i><sub>uncompensated</sub></span> was termed by Clausius the "uncompensated heat", though that does not accord with present-day terminology. Then one has</p>

<dl id="mwkA"><dd id="mwkQ"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt476" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":" T\\,\\mathrm{d}S=\\delta Q+T\\,\\mathrm{d}S_{\\mathrm{uncompensated}} > \\delta Q ."}}' id="mwkg"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle T\,\mathrm {d} S=\delta Q+T\,\mathrm {d} S_{\mathrm {uncompensated} }>\delta Q.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>T</mi>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mi>S</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mi>δ<!-- δ --></mi>
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>T</mi>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
        </mrow>
        <msub>
          <mi>S</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi mathvariant="normal">u</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">c</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>
              <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>></mo>
        <mi>δ<!-- δ --></mi>
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle T\,\mathrm {d} S=\delta Q+T\,\mathrm {d} S_{\mathrm {uncompensated} }>\delta Q.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0ab0ec92d9beb5c1005dcdc6a11dd9178eb8a369" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:36.306ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="T\,\mathrm {d} S=\delta Q+T\,\mathrm {d} S_{\mathrm {uncompensated} }>\delta Q."/></span><span about="#mwt476">
</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwkw">This leads to the statement</p>

<dl id="mwlA"><dd id="mwlQ"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt478" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":" T\\,\\mathrm{d}S \\geq \\delta Q \\quad{\\rm{(second\\,\\,law)}}\\,."}}' id="mwlg"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle T\,\mathrm {d} S\geq \delta Q\quad {\rm {(second\,\,law)}}\,.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>T</mi>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mi>S</mi>
        <mo>≥<!-- ≥ --></mo>
        <mi>δ<!-- δ --></mi>
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mspace width="1em"></mspace>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">c</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
            <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
            <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi>
            <mi mathvariant="normal">w</mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle T\,\mathrm {d} S\geq \delta Q\quad {\rm {(second\,\,law)}}\,.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/92b71a62bd6fac6cd9f39585a4b5ea4c67f464b0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:26.956ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="T\,\mathrm {d} S\geq \delta Q\quad {\rm {(second\,\,law)}}\,."/></span><span about="#mwt478">
</span></dd></dl>
<p id="mwlw">which is the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Second_law_of_thermodynamics" title="Second law of thermodynamics" id="mwmA">second law of thermodynamics</a> for closed systems.</p>

<p id="mwmQ">In non-equilibrium thermodynamics that approximates by assuming the hypothesis of local thermodynamic equilibrium, there is a special notation for this. The transfer of energy as heat is assumed to take place across an infinitesimal temperature difference, so that the system element and its surroundings have near enough the same temperature <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt79" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;T&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwmg"><i>T</i></span>. Then one writes</p>

<dl id="mwmw"><dd id="mwnA"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt480" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":" \\mathrm{d}S =\\mathrm{d}S_{\\mathrm e}+\\mathrm{d}S_{\\mathrm i}\\,,"}}' id="mwnQ"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \mathrm {d} S=\mathrm {d} S_{\mathrm {e} }+\mathrm {d} S_{\mathrm {i} }\,,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mi>S</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi>
        </mrow>
        <msub>
          <mi>S</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
