</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mw3A">with <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt118" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;V&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw3Q"><i>V</i></span> the volume of the system, which is a state variable. In general, for homogeneous systems,</p>
<dl id="mw3g"><dd id="mw3w"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt496" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\mathrm{d}U = T\\mathrm{d}S - P\\mathrm{d}V."}}' id="mw4A"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \mathrm {d} U=T\mathrm {d} S-P\mathrm {d} V.}">
