</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mw4Q">Associated with this differential equation is that the internal energy may be considered to be a function <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt120" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;U&apos;&apos; (&apos;&apos;S&apos;&apos;,&apos;&apos;V&apos;&apos;)"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw4g"><i>U</i> (<i>S</i>,<i>V</i>)</span> of its <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Thermodynamic_potential" title="Thermodynamic potential" id="mw4w">natural variables</a> <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt121" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;S&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw5A"><i>S</i></span> and <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt122" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;V&apos;&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mw5Q"><i>V</i></span>. The internal energy representation of the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Fundamental_thermodynamic_relation" title="Fundamental thermodynamic relation" id="mw5g">fundamental thermodynamic relation</a> is written</p>
<dl id="mw5w"><dd id="mw6A"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt498" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"U=U(S,V)."}}' id="mw6Q"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle U=U(S,V).}">
