<p id="mwASY">It is known that the temperature <span class="texhtml " about="#mwt171" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"math","href":"./Template:Math"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"&apos;&apos;T&apos;&apos;(&apos;&apos;S&apos;&apos;, &apos;&apos;P&apos;&apos;)"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwASc"><i>T</i>(<i>S</i>, <i>P</i>)</span> is identically stated by</p>

<dl id="mwASg"><dd id="mwASk"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt451" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\left(\\frac{\\partial H}{\\partial S}\\right)_P \\equiv T(S,P)\\,."}}' id="mwASo"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \left({\frac {\partial H}{\partial S}}\right)_{P}\equiv T(S,P)\,.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mrow>
            <mo>(</mo>
            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mfrac>
                <mrow>
                  <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
                  <mi>H</mi>
                </mrow>
                <mrow>
                  <mi mathvariant="normal">∂<!-- ∂ --></mi>
                  <mi>S</mi>
                </mrow>
              </mfrac>
            </mrow>
            <mo>)</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>P</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>≡<!-- ≡ --></mo>
        <mi>T</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi>S</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mspace width="thinmathspace"></mspace>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \left({\frac {\partial H}{\partial S}}\right)_{P}\equiv T(S,P)\,.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a24fc1e8c073e5f62cd58aefde0e6c2acb876b0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:20.962ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="\left({\frac {\partial H}{\partial S}}\right)_{P}\equiv T(S,P)\,."/></span><span about="#mwt451">
</span></dd></dl>

<p id="mwASs">Consequently,</p>

<dl id="mwASw"><dd id="mwAS0"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt453" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"\\Delta H=\\int_{S_1}^{S_2} T(S,P) \\mathrm dS\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\, \\text{at constant pressure.}"}}' id="mwAS4"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \Delta H=\int _{S_{1}}^{S_{2}}T(S,P)\mathrm {d} S\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,\,{\text{at constant pressure.}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ<!-- Δ --></mi>
        <mi>H</mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msubsup>
          <mo>∫<!-- ∫ --></mo>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <msub>
              <mi>S</mi>
              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
